<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Starzz 70, Mystics 67  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- Natalie Williams scored a season-high 30
points and had 13 rebounds to lead the Utah Starzz to a 70-67
victory over the Washington Mystics on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Williams added 13 rebounds for her seventh double-double in 10
games for the Starzz, who also got 14 points from Adrienne Goodson.
</P>
<P>
   Utah held a 14-point lead early in the second half and appeared
to be headed for an easy night until Nikki McCray helped Washington
make a game of it. She scored all of her team-leading 20 points in
the second half.
</P>
<P>
   The Mystics, who also got 19 points from Chamique Holdsclaw and
18 from Vicky Bullett, trimmed the Starzz's lead to two points
twice in the game's final 20 seconds -- at 67-65 and 69-67. But the
Starzz held on.
</P>
<P>
   Utah scored 21 points from the free-throw line, while Washington
made just 6-of-12. The Starzz, who led 31-22 at halftime, also
outrebounded the Mystics 35-27.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-06-18-00 0023 </TRAILER>
