<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-18 00:26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sparks 94, Fire 81  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Mwadi Mabika scored a career-high 26
points to help the Los Angeles Sparks stop a two-game losing streak
with a 94-81 victory over the expansion Portland Fire on Saturday
night.
</P>
<P>
   With stars Lisa Leslie and DeLisha Milton in foul trouble, the
smaller players picked up the slack for Los Angeles. Guard Tamecka
Dixon scored 24 points and Mabika added 10 rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   Sylvia Crawley scored 17 points and Sophia Witherspoon and
Vanessa Nygaard each had 16 to lead the Fire, which lost its fifth
straight and fell to 1-6, the worst record in the Western
Conference.
</P>
<P>
   Leslie, who scored just five points in the first half after
picking up her third foul with 6:29 left, finished with 15 points.
Fellow Olympian Milton played just 17 minutes and had three points.
</P>
<P>
   The Fire took an early 9-8 lead, but Los Angeles went ahead for
good with an 18-4 run.
</P>
<P>
   Portland cut the lead to 61-60 on a driving layup by rookie
Stacey Thomas with 13:35 to go in the game, but the Fire couldn't
get closer than three the rest of the way.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-06-18-00 0026 </TRAILER>
