<HEADLINE> Top of Our Game Wins Sire Stakes  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Top of Our Game beat She's An I Full by
two lengths Saturday in the $100,000 California Sire Stakes for
3-year-old fillies at Hollywood Park.
</P>
<P>
   Top of Our Game, ridden by David Flores, ran 1 1-16 miles on the
turf course in 1:41.41, and paid $3.60, $2.40 and $2.10.
</P>
<P>
   She's An I Full returned $2.80 and $2.10, and Blonde Bounty paid
$2.20 to show.
</P>
</TEXT>
