<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-18 00:46 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Crew 0, Rapids 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER (AP) -- Colorado Rapids goalkeeper Adin Brown made six
saves and the Columbus Crew's Matt Napoleon saved three shots as
the teams played a scoreless tie Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Colorado tied a club record with 28 shots but only three were on
goal, including a missed penalty kick by Junior Agogo.
</P>
<P>
   Columbus nearly scored in the 14th minute on a free kick by
Robert Warzycha, but Brown blocked the shot with one hand.
</P>
<P>
   In the 73rd minute, Brown blocked a shot by Jason Farrell and
was on the ground when the ball bounced back to the Crew's Dante
Washington, only 10 yards out. But Washington's kick sailed over
the crossbar.
</P>
<P>
   Columbus lost forward Brian McBride, a starter on the U.S.
national team, in the 42nd minute with a facial injury. He was
replaced by Washington.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
