<SUBHEAD>
Poll Finds Abortion Views Conflicted
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- A majority of Americans believe abortion is murder, but
more than two-thirds think the decision to have one must be left to a woman and
her doctor, according to a Los Angeles Times poll released today.The poll is
full of responses that seem contradictory. Sixty-five percent of those
questioned oppose a constitutional amendment banning abortion but only 43
percent support the landmark Roe vs. Wade Supreme Court decision. More than half
of the 57 percent of respondents who think abortion is murder also believe women
should have the right to choose. The Times surveyed 2,071 Americans by telephone
from June 8 through Tuesday.
</P>
