thousands dead in the Horn of Africa. The accord, reached after more than two
weeks of talks punctuated by fighting on the front, does not bring a definitive
end to the 25 months of fighting between the African neighbors, but allows a
reprieve while negotiators delineate the bitterly disputed frontier. The accord,
mediated by the Organization of African Unity, calls for international
