<HEADLINE> NATO Detonates Kosovo Packages  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PRISTINA, Yugoslavia (AP) -- British bomb experts blew up four
suspicious packages inside a car parked in front of Pristina's main
hotel Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   U.N. police spokesman Charley Johnson said police were tipped
off shortly before noon that a bomb had been planted in a red car
outside the Grand Hotel in downtown Pristina and they would go off
within 10 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Detonation experts serving with the NATO-led Kosovo peacekeeping
force subsequently blew up four packages inside the vehicle.
</P>
<P>
   The entire downtown area of Pristina was cordoned off by
peacekeepers and U.N. police, preventing reporters and others from
getting closer to the scene.
</P>
</TEXT>
