<HEADLINE> Mizumaki Wins Tamanoi Yomiuri Open  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NISHINOMIYA, Japan (AP) -- Yoshinori Mizumaki shot a 5-under-par
67 Sunday and won the Tamanoi Yomiuri Open by three strokes.
</P>
<P>
   Mizumaki, teeing off with a two-shot lead, birdied the first
three holes but bogeyed the eighth. On the back nine, he added
three more birdies on his way to a 17-under 271 total.
</P>
<P>
   For his first victory of the season and seventh overall,
Mizumaki earned $169,800 from a purse of $849,000.
</P>
<P>
   First-round leader Hisayuki Sasaki birdied all four par-5s in a
bogey-free round of 66 and finished second at 14-under 274.
</P>
<P>
   Seiki Okuda had the day's best round of 64 for a share of
seventh at 278.
</P>
