spokeswoman at St. James's Palace, the prince's London residence, confirmed that
Charles is hosting the dinner Tuesday at the new headquarters of the Prince's
Foundation charity, but refused to say whether Parker Bowles would attend. Her
presence would be another landmark in an increasingly successful campaign by
Charles to gain public acceptability for Parker Bowles.
</P>
