Tiger Woods Holds 10-Stroke Lead
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   PEBBLE BEACH, Calif. (AP) -- With incredible shots and unlikely birdies,
Tiger Woods hit an even-par 71 yesterday to build a 10-stroke lead after three
rounds, the largest 54-hole margin in U.S. Open history. ''The tough conditions,
I thought, played into my hands,'' Woods said about the whipping winds, thick
rough and rock-hard greens. ''I played solid golf.'' He is at 8-under 205, 10
strokes clear of two-time U.S. Open champion Ernie Els.
AP NewsBrief by DAVID GOODMAN 
