after his release from detention in a psychiatric hospital, where he was
injected with nerve-destroying drugs, a human rights group said today. Su Gang,
a 32-year-old computer engineer, was in fine health before he was sent to the
hospital on May 23 but was weak, slow, stiff-limbed and unable to eat when he
was released eight days later, the Information Center for Human Rights and
Democracy said, quoting Su's father, Su De'an. Su died of heart failure on June
10, less than two weeks after his release.
