   BAILEY, Colo. (AP) -- Government leaders today are assessing damage to the
environment caused by two wildfires burning in the foothills of the Rocky
Mountains. The blazes have blackened 21,000 acres and destroyed 54 homes since
Monday. Rain and snow on the narrow mountain roads kept most firefighters from a
blaze east of Rocky Mountain National Park yesterday. One crew spent the night
near the fire site, and officials said firefighters expect to have it contained
today. The second fire, about 35 miles southwest of Denver, is expected to be
contained by Wednesday.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
N. Korea: U.S. Raising Military Tension
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   SEOUL, South Korea (AP) -- Following a United States announcement saying it
has no plans to withdraw its troops from South Korea, North Korea today accused
the Clinton administration of increasing the danger of a war on the Korean
peninsula. ''The U.S. imperialists pretend to be interested in peace...However,
all their acts only result in increasing the danger of war and escalating the
tensions,'' said Rodong Sinmun, a newspaper for the ruling (North) Korean
Workers' Party.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
British Airport Delays Continue
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- Passengers at airports across Britain, particularly Heathrow
and Glasgow, suffered delays of up to five hours today as airports struggled to
get back to normal after a computer breakdown yesterday. Delays decreased during
the day, with most flights leaving Heathrow within about one hour of the
scheduled time by afternoon. British Airways and British Midland reported
canceling more than 30 flights, mainly domestic and to continental Europe.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Hewitt Beats Sampras at Queens
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- Australian Lleyton Hewitt beat six-time Wimbledon champion
Pete Sampras 6-4, 6-4 today to win the Queen's Club grasscourt tournament. The
19-year-old Hewitt, who beat Sampras for the first time in four meetings,
defeated the defending tournament champion with a strong return game. Hewitt,
who won his fourth title of the season, also had nine aces to five for Sampras
in this traditional warmup for Wimbledon.
AP NewsBrief by DAVID GOODMAN 
