British Airport Delays Continue
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- Passengers at airports across Britain, particularly Heathrow
and Glasgow, suffered delays of up to five hours today as airports struggled to
get back to normal after a computer breakdown yesterday. Delays decreased during
the day, with most flights leaving Heathrow within about one hour of the
scheduled time by afternoon. British Airways and British Midland reported
canceling more than 30 flights, mainly domestic and to continental Europe.
</P>
