</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   LE MANS, France (AP) -- Emmanuele Pirro drove Audi to its first victory in
the Le Mans 24-Hour race today, leading a sweep of the podium for the German
auto maker. The car of Pirro, Germany's Frank Biela and Denmark's Tom Kristensen
completed 368 laps. Finishing one lap back was France's Laurent Aiello,
Britain's Allan McNish and Monaco's Stephane Ortelli, the 1998 winners for
Porsche, who started from the pole position and led early.
