<HEADLINE> Boy Arrested in Fatal Ohio Fire  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- A 17-year-old boy told police he threw a
firework into the duplex where an early morning fire Saturday
killed three children and critically injured their mother,
officials said.
</P>
<P>
   Mitchell Sexton Jr. was arrested Saturday night and charged with
three counts of involuntary manslaughter and one count of felonious
assault.
</P>
<P>
   ''He admitted to us he threw a firework into the house,''
homicide detective Robert Viduya said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Cynthia Campbell, 38, remained in critical condition Sunday with
second-degree burns over half her body, an Ohio State University
Medical Center spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
   She escaped by jumping from an upstairs window. Her children,
ages 4, 2 and 11 months, were trapped inside and died of smoke
inhalation, officials said. Their father was gone from the house
when the fire broke out.
</P>
<P>
   Neighbors told police Sexton was upset with someone who had been
staying at the house and had threatened to set it on fire.
</P>
