<HEADLINE> Lakewood man drowns in Lake Carasaljo  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   LAKEWOOD, N.J., (AP) - A 22-year-old man trying to beat the heat
drowned when he apparently became exhausted swimming across Lake
Carasaljo, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Benjamin Ramirez, of Lakewood, was swimming with two friends
about 3:20 p.m. on Saturday when he began struggling and slipped
beneath the surface of the large lake.
</P>
<P>
   They were swimming from a beach to a spot on the other side of
the lake where there are no lifeguards.
</P>
<P>
   ''My best guess is - and that's what this is - is that he
probably exhausted himself and couldn't go any farther,'' Lt. John
Garruto said.
</P>
<P>
   When the victim's two friends reached the other side of the
lake, they looked back and saw Ramirez struggling in the water. One
of them swam back to Ramirez, but had to let go because Ramirez was
pulling him under the water.
</P>
<P>
   Ramirez' body was recovered about an hour later. An autopsy was
to be performed Sunday.
</P>
</TEXT>
