<HEADLINE> Albright Addresses Graduates  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON (AP) -- America must play a leading role to protect the
rights of women and workers around the world, Secretary of State
Madeleine K. Albright told graduates at Northeastern University.
</P>
<P>
   Addressing the school's 98th commencement Saturday, Albright
said she was proud of American foreign policy accomplishments in
the Middle East, the Korean peninsula and Northern Ireland. But she
said more can be done.
</P>
