<P>
   In recalling her experience as secretary of state, Albright said
she will most remember not heads of state but people victimized by
violence and suffering.
</P>
<P>
   ''I have been called the world's most powerful woman, but when a
mother dying of AIDS in Africa asked me to be sure her children
were cared for -- I lacked even the power of speech, because I did
not know what I could honestly say,'' Albright said.
</P>
