<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-18 21:28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton Celebrates Father's Day  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- His daughter, Chelsea, at his side, President
Clinton began Father's Day at church. The sermon: The parable of
the prodigal son, who squanders his inheritance but is welcomed
home by a forgiving father.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton, wearing a navy blue tie, ignored shouted questions
about security breaches at Los Alamos National Laboratory in New
Mexico. On her way out of Foundry United Methodist Church, Chelsea
waved to reporters and cameramen and exclaimed ''Happy Father's
Day'' before climbing into a limousine.
</P>
<P>
   Back at the White House, Clinton, first lady Hillary Rodham
Clinton, Chelsea and several other friends spent a quiet afternoon
together. In the evening, the president hastily called his
entourage together for a trip to a suburban golf course with
Commerce Secretary William M. Daley. Daley was named Vice President
Gore's new campaign chief earlier this week.
</P>
<P>
   Their game lasted only one hour and five holes after rain cut it
short.
</P>
<P>
   Later, Clinton called golfer Tiger Woods from the White House to
congratulate him on his victory Sunday at the U.S. Open, said
deputy press secretary Jim Kennedy. Kennedy did not know details of
the conversation.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton was expected to finish the day with his family at a
White House screening of ''The Patriot,'' a soon-to-be-released
movie starring Mel Gibson.
</P>
<P>
   On Saturday, the president played golf with his stepfather, Dick
Kelley, and several others willing to brave dark storm clouds and
venture out to a course in Fairfax, Va. In between shots, Clinton
draped his arm around his stepfather's shoulder. Rain cut that game
short, too.
</P>
</TEXT>
